rows.name: Quick Start
rows.pagesPluginContent:
PIXI-UI

It is a library that contains commonly used UI components, that are extensible to allow them to be used in any project

Here are some useful resources: - [Full docs](https://pixijs.io/ui/) - [Github Repo](https://github.com/pixijs/ui) - [Storybook](https://pixijs.io/ui/storybook/) ## Install ```sh npm install @pixijs/ui ``` There is no default export. The correct way to import pixi-ui is: ```js import { Button, Layout, ScrollBox } from '@pixijs/ui'; ``` To use any of the components you can go to it's page and copypaste the example code to your project.
